// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// "Depth present, color missing" 1-frame flicker (PASS0 draws a primitive into depth; PASS1
// rebuilds the render list from scratch and false-negative-HiZ-culls it because a HiZ INPUT
// -- pyramid / bounding sphere / visibility bitmap -- is stale for one frame; window opened by
// parallel queues or by extra passes perturbing the frame timeline). cmd1.w bit0 = "added in PASS0"
// (set at the "Mark as added" line). The two former compile-time toggles are now RUNTIME flags in
// pushConstants.flags (set per RendererInstance from KeepPass0ForRendering / KeepPass0InPass1):
//
//   FLAG_KEEP_PASS0_FOR_RENDERING (bit 5, see const below) : Variante (a), default ON. Keep
//     PASS0-committed primitives in the RENDER list, but drive the visibility bitmap from the TRUE
//     HiZ result -> occlusion culling stays intact, only ~1 transition frame of depth-tested
//     overdraw. Cheap correctness net against 1-frame staleness races (NOT the deterministic
//     skinned false-cull -- that is fixed by TpvScene3D.UseConservativeSkinnedBounds).
//
//   FLAG_KEEP_PASS0_IN_PASS1 (bit 6, see const below) : DIAGNOSTIC ONLY, default OFF. Skip the PASS1
//     HiZ test entirely for PASS0-committed primitives AND mark them visible -> BREAKS occlusion
//     culling (once-visible/in-frustum geometry never gets occlusion-culled again, growing overdraw).
//     Kills the flicker BUT breaks occlusion culling: such primitives also get marked visible in
//     the output visibility bitmap, so next frame's PASS0 redraws them -> once-visible/in-frustum
//     geometry is never occlusion-culled again (growing overdraw). So, diagnostic only.
//
// Richtung-2 root-cause probe: on the bad frame, dump the PASS1 object-level HiZ inputs for any
// NEAR-CAMERA PASS0-committed primitive (cmd1.w bit0 -> its depth is already in the buffer) that
// the HiZ test wants to occlusion-cull == exactly the "depth present, color missing" flicker event.
// Self-triggering + distance-gated (DEBUG_PASS0_HIZ_DROP_MAX_DISTANCE) so it only fires for the
// player's parts -> stays rare -> does NOT drop to the ~1-FPS regime where the race stops
// reproducing. Needs the validation layer + DebugPrintf at runtime (run planetgame1 with
// --force-use-validation-layers); grep the log for "HIZDROP".
//#define DEBUG_PASS0_HIZ_DROP_PRINTF
#define DEBUG_PASS0_HIZ_DROP_MAX_DISTANCE 25.0

// Conservative Hi-Z occlusion sample over the projected AABB (center + 4 corners) instead
// of a single AABB-center texel.
//#define HIZ_CONSERVATIVE_FOOTPRINT

